&lt;p class=&quot;PDq2pG_selectionAnchorContainer&quot; data-start=&quot;377&quot; data-end=&quot;646&quot;&gt;US President Donald Trump on Monday declared that Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu would not be arrested while visiting the United States, amid renewed debate over an International Criminal Court (ICC) arrest warrant against the Israeli leader.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;648&quot; data-end=&quot;796&quot;&gt;In a post on Truth Social, Trump said, &quot;Benjamin Netanyahu will not be arrested, in any way, shape, or form, while in the United States of America.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;798&quot; data-end=&quot;1034&quot;&gt;Although Trump did not directly mention New York City Mayor Zohran Mamdani, the statement came days after the mayor said city officials were examining whether local authorities could act on the ICC warrant if Netanyahu visited New York.&lt;/p&gt;
